Utterance: Hello. My name is Rakshya. I will be your nurse for today.
Hey! What's up?
what bring you here today?
Those idiot cops brought me here. I don't need to be here but the front desk guy said that they have to check me out. Like I'm some sort of book in the history of atlases.
Do you have any anxiety?

I'm not anxious or paranoid or whatever. I mean, I just have a really really fine-tuned sense of, like, OK, now they're coming for me, the government agents, and I have to be on the look out, 'cause no way am I being snatched up, not a chance.
Can you tell me more about the government agents?

I mean, what do you want to know? I just had a hunch they were in one of those cars, waiting to scoop me up and throw me in solitary. They know I'm enlightened and if my writings get out, boom, their secrets are overthrown. Not that I'm gonna let them stop me.
Do you See or hear the voice that other other people's does not see?
Do you ever hear things that others do not hear?
No. I told you what happened earlier tonight. I wasn't seeing stuff or hearing voices. This is the most clear-headed I've ever been in my life.
Do you use substances?
I do coke, I drink . . . that's really it. I like doing the same things over and over. I get in my groove with it.
Tell me about your most recent substance use?
I haven't been anything but sober for like, four days. I know I seem like I'm on something, but I'm just this way naturally.
What is your sleeping pattern?
I usually only need a couple hours. These past four days? I haven't slept a wink. Not even tired. I'm the frickin' man, I know.
How is your current mood?
I am 100% letting the good times roll. Couldn't be better.
Tell me about your energy and mood?
Amazing! I feel great! I'm bursting at the gills--is, is that what people say? Up, up to the gills? Step right up, boys and gills!
Tell me about your energy?
How have your energy levels been?
Awesome! I mean, I'm just a high energy kind of guy, a lot of the time. But this week especially I've felt, like, crazy up and up, and I love it. I just love it. I feel like I could lift a horse.
Do you have any present health condition?
Do you have any acute medical concerns?

My health is fine, OK? Like, I'm not here because of my health. The cops brought me here for lord knows what, and my only major health thing has ever been my depression, but that's six feet under now, so we're good.
What is your typical mood look like?
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
How often your mood changes?
I'm not keeping track or anything, but maybe a couple times a year? I don't know. This is a really nice room. I really like this room.
Can you tell me about your last period of depression?

It seems like you're probing into some, uh, rather sensitive territory here. The last time I was depressed--uh, just saying the word sucks--it lasted a long time. I clawed my way out. It was dark. That's it. I'm not gonna say anything else.
Can you tell me more about your depression diagnosis?

I mean, that doctor was a buffoon, but I get where he was coming from -- I had just tried to kill myself. That doesn't necessarily scream NOT depressed, you know? Like, your eyeballs are your eyeballs. You see what you see.
How was your depression treated?
That quack of a doctor put me on antidepressants. Yeah, sure took a lot of self-interrogation to write stuff on a pad. I mean, my god. No intellect whatsoever.
Do you have any medication allergies?

I don't have any, I don't think, though I haven't really had that many meds in my life. Maybe if you gave me, like, Zorpizol I would grow, you know -- Zorps everywhere. Zorp Zorp. Like, that's the sound of Zorps, they go, Zooooorp.
What antidepressant were you taking?
I don't remember what they were called, sorry. In my head I call them Suck Pills. Suckitol. Suckizol. For suckitis. Hah!
Did you have any side effects with the medication?
Yeah, the antidepressos did some stuff to me. Whatever. Bullcrap little -- just -- just stupid, stupid stuff. No one needs 'em.
What other Home medication do you take besides antidepressant?
None. The only thing I ever took a while back were antidepressants.
What kind of side effects do you have with antidepressants?
Dude, just drop it, OK? It doesn't matter. Jeez Louise.
Have you ever attempt suicide before?
Yeah. Yeah, I attempted suicide. It's so dumb. You can't get through life like that. You gotta say yes to stuff, you know?
When was your last time you attempted suicide?
Oh, man, like . . . 3 years ago? I don't think you're really understanding how in the past it is.
Do you ever want to be dead?
No! Really, that's not me. That's not -- it gets like -- obviously, when you're depressed, you think like that, sure. But that's not me anymore, so whatever. I'm not worried about it.
Do you ever think others would be better off without you?
. . . No. Do I feel like that? No. That's all I care to say. No.
Do you have Present thought of suicide?
No, my god, no, that's not -- you're reading too much into things. That was a long time ago. I love my life and I'm going to live it hard. I've already wasted too much time wanting to die.
can you tell me more about your Suicide attempt that you had done for first time?
I don't know what you want me to say, it was -- I just don't wanna talk about it, OK? I just, I don't -- just focus on the present. This is all that's going on with me.
Did you attempt suicide other than that?
Just the once . . . and you really don't have to worry about me like that.
Are you thinking of self-harming without intending to die?
No, not at all. Such a bummer question. I only really got like that during my one suicide attempt. One as in done.
Are thinking of any homicidal urges?
Have you ever felt like killing someone?
What? Are you serious? No. I feel bad if I accidentally bump into somebody in a hallway. I'm a vessel of love. It's all there.
What is your perception of Mental Health?

My brain is superb, honestly. It's frickin' cotton candy and sports car up there. Don't worry about me. Like, yeah, I was depressed before, if that's what you're asking. But that's as dead as a doornail, hangnail, all the nails.
Have any other people notice that your mood or energy shifts?
Who knows what other people notice? Personally, I notice everything, but you can't expect every chump on the street to be enlightened.
Do you ever have excessive irritability or anger?
Sure, anger is a flower. I am a man of emotion. I feel everything, probably more than anybody else on earth. If a scamp interferes with my vibes, the anger blooms.
Do you have any arguments are fights?
Have you been in fights or arguments?
My proverbial temper is lost on occasion. But all I do is argue! I'm not hurting anybody. My hands are clean.
Have you noticed any changes in speed of moving or speaking?
I mean, nah, I'm just a super quick guy in general. I like to get things done and keep 'em moving. Talk fast, walk fast, all that. What can I say, some horses weren't meant for carriages.
Do you have any racing thoughts?
Like a greyhound. Hyah! Hyah! But it works out great, because I'm working on this massive poem that's all about--well, it's gonna blow people's minds.
what Kind of activities you are interested and that gives you a pleasure?

I've always been super interested in literature, like making meaning of the world we live in. Kinda of bleeds into my philosophical meanderings you know. The epic poem I'm working on is super exciting, like world-changing kind of stuff. Forget your chicken scratch is all I'm saying.
Do you have any pleasure or interest in typical activities?

Heck yeah, my life is the best. There's joy everywhere. There's joy in this hospital room, not that you would know much about that. Yeah, you really just gotta keep an eye out for it, my friend. Just squint and you'll see it. (Clarified to if I have experienced pleasure and interest in typical activities.)
Have you experienced pleasure or interest in typical activities?
Tell me about your ability to concentrate?

Oh, I've been laser-focused lately. On my poetry, that is. On my friends' projects. I told you we're thinking about making this community art center? It would be so sick. We'll see. It's all in the works.
Do you have any change in social activity?
My social game has been through the roof in the last week. Not to be braggadocio, but I dosey doe with the best of them.
Do you have any change in your sexual activity?
My carnal business has definitely amped up in the past week! And I'm not complaining, either. It's been totally awesome. Friends and strangers, the sexy time has been unreal.
What are your spending habits?
Well, I'm spending on the stuff that matters. I'm talking about a little cocaine here, some rare books there. I help my friends out however I can because you know? I'm a giver.
What is a financial status?
What is your financial situation?
My finances are good! My parents give me some dough every now and then, I don't have to work . . . it's pretty stellar, ideal even!
Do you work?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
What did your occupation?

In the past--I worked at a pizza place once. Another time my dad's friend let me work at his office. I put Christmas trees on people's cars. I worked at an insurance office for like two weeks one time.
Do we ever drink alcohol?
Yeah, like everyone on earth. There's nothing unnatural about drinking potato juice. That's what it is, you know.
Do you drink alcohol?
Yeah, like everyone on earth. There's nothing unnatural about drinking potato juice. That's what it is, you know.
Tell me more about the potato juice?
No matching questions found.
when you say potato juice, what does that mean?

How often you drink alcohol?

Not often -- 2 or 3 times a week, I guess. It's more of a party vibe than anything. I drink more when I'm down, but I'm not down anymore! It's all loose goose these days. I'm not, like, waking up with the hair of the dog. That's like, no hair and no dogs for me, thank you.
How often do you do drugs?
I'm no math whiz, pop, bang!--but I probably do a couple lines a couple times a week.
What is your method of transportation?
Oh, how do I get around? I'm cruising the streets in my car. I got it when I turned sixteen and that thing's like a brother to me.
How is your appetite lately?
Not hungry at all. That's just kinda how I am. This week especially, I've only needed like, a tiny meal a day.
How much fluid do you drink a day?
How much liquid do you drink in a day?
I don't know, I don't have, like, a cup measurer. I just have a glass or two at some point in the day, I'd guess.
How much fluid I drink per day.
How often you do you take caffeine?
Do I look like a guy who needs caffeine? This is au naturale, baby. I don't need no crushed up bean juice that tastes like tree poop.
Tell me about your level of Education?
I did a year in college a while back.
Do you have easy access to healthcare?
Yeah, I'm on my parents' insurance. It's such a crock, though, these insurance goons and the Super Pharm Outlet Malls of America . . .
Tell me about your current living situation?

It's pretty perfect, honestly. No rent, no bills, no dusting. I just crash in my car or at a friends' place or wherever, then I wake up and start my day. Boom. Did you know the kookaburra never sleeps in the same tree twice? I think most people would make better decisions if they mimicked ornithology.
Tell me about your support system

My friends are a lot better at listening and getting me than my family is. My folks think I'm a strung out junkie who belongs in rehab. They don't know the difference between a casual partier and street vermin. I'm a vibe rider, you know? Goddang, it gets me riled up to talk about. They're just imbeciles.
Do you have any history of abuse?
Dang, are you serious?! No, not at all. Dang, what a wet blanket question. No, that's never happened to me. Dang. Screwin' up the vibes.
I am sorry about that.
That's super cool of you, thanks!
Does your family has any mental illness
No . . . I couldn't tell you anything about my birth parents, but my real parents are pretty sane. They're kinda, like, massive normies. Wouldn't know art if it hit 'em in the balls.
Do you have any recent change in your vision?
Have you noticed changes in your behavior?
I'm so stoked on life lately that I've been moving pretty fast. It's like--boom, boom, boom!
If I have had behavioral changes
Has your vision changed recently?
Peachy keen! I can see you just fine.
Do you feel any palpitation?
No, the drumbeat is steady.
Do you have any change in your hair?
The hair of my body has changed not at all. Not at all has the hair of my body changed. Change in the pocket goes jingle jangle jong. Brass monkeys can do nothing but bang the gong!
How is your bowel movement?
Methinks mepoop's been all good, no issues, no change.
Do you have any legal troubles?
Not at all! I'm the patron saint of innocence! Hah. No, really though, I've never gotten so much as a ticket.
Tell me about your self concept

I see myself as this visionary poet who's going to rock the world once his work is published. I see a killer head of hair that ladies just can't resist. I see an enlightened soul that shines like stained-glass. Amen, let the choir sing.
